	  	<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Content style guide</h1>


	  	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		  Always follow the GOV.UK <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/style-guide/a-to-z-of-gov-uk-style">style guide</a> and use <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/content-design/writing-for-gov-uk#plain-english">plain English</a> to make your writing as easy to understand as possible, for as many people as possible. Teachers included.
		</p>

		<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Academic, calendar or financial year</h1>
		<p class="govuk-body-m">Always say which type of year you’re referring to. </p>

		<div class="govuk-inset-text">‘You can claim back the repayments you made in the last financial year.’</div>


		<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Date ranges</h1>
		<p class="govuk-body-m">Use words (like ‘to’) instead of a dash or slash in date ranges. It’s easier to read and better for screen readers.</p>

		<div class="govuk-inset-text">‘The financial year 2019 to 2020’</div>
		<div class="govuk-inset-text">‘Between 6 April 2018 and 5 April 2019’</div>

		<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Capitalisation of service names</h1>
		<p class="govuk-body-m">Only capitalise the first letter of the name.</p>

		<div class="govuk-inset-text">The Claim additional payments for teaching team</div>
		<div class="govuk-inset-text">The teachers’ service ‘Claim back your student loan repayments’</div>
		<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">‘You and ‘we’</h1>
		<p class="govuk-body-m">The claimant is always ‘you’.</p>

		<p class="govuk-body-m">We are the Department for Education. Use ‘we’ instead of ‘the Department’ or ‘DfE’ when it’s clear who you’re referring to. </p>

		<div class="govuk-inset-text">‘We’ve received your claim’</div>

		<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Approved words and phrases</h1>
		<p class="govuk-body-m">If you’re replying to a claimant use the language they’ve used. Otherwise, use the following.</p>

		<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
			<li>Claim (not apply or application)</li>
			<li>Claimant (not applicant, user or customer)</li>
			<li>Claim a payment for teaching maths or physics (not retention payments)</li>
			<li>Claim back your student loan repayments (not student loan reimbursement)</li>
			<li>Computing (not computer science)</li>
			<li>Confirm your identity (when used generally)</li>
			<li>Employed to teach at (not teach at or employed at)</li>
			<li>Financial year (not tax year)</li>
			<li>Initial teacher training </li>
			<li>Make a decision on a claim </li>
			<li>Maths (not mathematics)</li>
			<li>Process, review, approve or reject a claim</li>
			<li>Send or complete a claim (not submit)</li>
			<li>Start a claim</li>
			<li>Tasks (not checks)</li>
			<li>Undo a decision on a claim</li>
			<li>Verify your identity (using GOV.UK Verify)</li>
		</ul>

